body:
I know this was a horrible game and i know i wasn't using my brain but talked to riot support about my ban and they gave me 3 times of my game that i did bad and purposely inted which isn't even correct because here we are at 4:45 i had solo engaged 2 enemies which was correct but that was a stupid mistake as i was mistaken on what my support went 2nd so that was a bit of miscommunication while the shaco sat there watching me o well it happens. 2nd 5:35 running under mid lane turret which was correct but it was because i had been inting prior because of my dumb decisions and dumb plays so i decided to execute myself a few times so it wouldn't be as much as a loss for our team. 3rd at 6:20 i had apparently ran into 4 enemies under mid turret which wasn't even correct because at 6:20 i had actually helped our rengar and vlad get kills in mid lane so that was a bit confusing for a reason for being banned. In the end i know i went 1/23/5 but is that really a purpose int? I can vouge i had a bad game every has a bad game but getting a 14 day ban for this 1st offense for purpose inting apparently i know i can be a little toxic from time to time in retaliation to people playing badly but this event made me realize i had just had a bad game and got flamed hard out of and report because of it so i understand the pains of a bad game and regret my past reports for having bad games but honestly how would a 1/23/5 game with unjustified times of apparent inting be seen as an instant 14 day ban no don't do it again otherwise you'll get banned flat 14 day ban for unjustified terms.
Hope i can get some insight and support on this situation as the riot employees where no help yours truly
